Two of the four top students at the Coast in the 2016 KCSE exam were treated to a free holiday at the Pride Inn Beach Resort on Saturday.Mariam Salim and Fatuma Mohammed scored straight As with 81 points each from Sheikh Khalifa Secondary School. The other two A plain achievers from Coast were Memon High School&rsquo;s Maria Harunani and Abdulkader Shaffi Bagha.Salim and Mohamed, two best friends, have been acting like twins, and even scored the same marks in all the subjects they did. Pride Inn&rsquo;s deputy sales and marketing manager Sammy Ogweno said the offer is part of the hotel chain&rsquo;s efforts to support local tourism and boost education.